President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his Administration. 

- Paul Dabbar of New York is nominated to be Under Secretary for Science, Department of Energy. He currently works as the Managing Director for Mergers & Acquisitions for J.P. Morgan, with extensive investment experience in various energy sectors. He has also served as a nuclear submarine officer and currently sits on the Department of Energy Environmental Management Advisory Board.

- Mark Wesley Menezes of Virginia is nominated to be Under Secretary of the Department of Energy. He is currently the Vice President of Federal Relations for Berkshire Hathaway Energy and has previously worked as a partner at Hunton & Williams and as Chief Counsel for the U.S. House Committee on Energy and Commerce.

- Dennis Shea of Virginia is nominated to be Deputy United States Trade Representative, Geneva Office, with the Rank of Ambassador. He currently serves as the Vice Chairman of the United States-China Economic and Security Review Commission and has extensive background in law and public policy.

- David B. Muhlhausen of Virginia is appointed as Director of the National Institute of Justice, Department of Justice. He is currently a research fellow at the Heritage Foundation and has expertise in using empirical research to formulate and evaluate government policies, particularly in the field of criminal justice. He holds a doctorate in public policy and has taught at George Mason University.

These nominations and appointments are subject to confirmation by the Senate.